Walkthrough - Cognitive Architecture with Dual-Channel Output
This document outlines the verification of the Cognitive Architecture, demonstrating the functionality of the Pattern Recognition Layer, Three-Threaded Braiding, and Dual-Channel Renderer.

Verification Results
Automated Tests
Ran python test_architecture.py to verify individual components.

Pattern Recognition: Correctly identifies archetypes based on keywords.
Structural Thread: Detects logical connectors and assigns scores.
Metabolic Thread: Calculates cost based on input length.
Social Thread: Evaluates sentiment keywords.
Braider: Successfully aggregates thread outputs.
Renderer: Produces both Symbolic and Narrative formats.
Result: All 6 tests passed.

Manual Verification (Demo)
Ran python main.py with the input signal:

"We should collaborate to help the community because it is good."

